{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"api_error_status":null,"duration_ms":694315,"duration_api_ms":481891,"num_turns":60,"result":"All files are in place. Here's the concise summary:\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n### Root causes fixed\n\n1. **`detect_non_service_native_project` too aggressive** (`full_migrate.py`): `pyproject.toml` scored 5 native points, README keywords added 4 more, and the subdirectory Dockerfile added 2 more (total 11). The function never credited `EXPOSE` in the Dockerfile as a service indicator, so lilbee was incorrectly rejected as a CLI/SDK project despite having a REST API on port 8000.\n\n   **Fix**: Added `service_score += 5` when the Dockerfile contains `EXPOSE <port>`. This brings lilbee's scores to native=11, service=8, failing the `native >= service + 5` threshold.\n\n2. **`apply_post_write` skips existing placeholder files** (`full_migrate.py`): `bm.write_files` writes a placeholder `Dockerfile.template` first; then `apply_post_write` sees the file exists and skips it (`if path.exists(): continue`), leaving the placeholder in place forever.\n\n   **Fix**: Added `_is_placeholder_file()` that detects the known placeholder markers, and changed `apply_post_write` to overwrite files that are still placeholders.\n\n3. **`SERVICE_README_HINTS` missing API-service hints**: Added `\"rest api\"`, `\"mcp server\"`, `\"api server\"` to the service hints tuple (cosmetic improvement).\n\n4. **`Dockerfile.template` needed manual repair**: Previous run left the placeholder. Written the real upstream Dockerfile using `SOURCE_VERSION` (build system's auto-injected arg) and `CMD [\"serve\"]` instead of `CMD [\"--help\"]`. Removed the extra `v` prefix in the download URL (upstream tag is `v0.6.66b456`, not `vv0.6.66b456`).\n\n### Changed files\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `scripts/full_migrate.py` | `detect_non_service_native_project`: EXPOSE→+5 service_score; `apply_post_write`: skip only non-placeholders; `SERVICE_README_HINTS`